description: At Psykick, we offer a range of services designed to cater to diverse needs and preferences: Individual Therapy: One-on-one sessions with our experienced professionals, tailored to address specific concerns and goals. Couples Therapy: Joint sessions for couples seeking to improve communication, resolve conflicts, and strengthen their relationship. Family Therapy: Sessions involving multiple family members, aimed at promoting healthy communication, resolving conflicts, and fostering a supportive environment. Group Therapy: Small group sessions focused on specific topics, such as anxiety, depression,  providing a sense of community and support. Online Support Groups: Moderated online forums for individuals to connect with others who share similar experiences and challenges. Our team of professionals at Psykick comprises licensed therapists, counsellors, and psychologists with extensive experience in addressing a wide range of mental health concerns. Our experts are trained in evidence-based therapies and approaches, ensuring that our clients receive the most effective and up-to-date care. Our team's diverse expertise enables us to cater to various needs, including: Anxiety and Depression: Our professionals are skilled in addressing anxiety disorders, depression, and mood disorders, helping clients develop coping mechanisms and strategies: We provide a safe and supportive environment for individuals who have experienced trauma, offering specialised therapies to facilitate mental  healing and recovery. Relationship Issues: Our team helps individuals and families navigate relationship challenges, including couples therapy, family therapy, and conflict resolution. Child and Adolescent Mental Health: Our experts are trained to address the unique needs of children and adolescents, providing guidance on developmental issues, behavioural concerns, and emotional well-being and healthiness.

description:
It's not a great feeling to be anxious. And when you are, it's tough to meditate without having the stressful thoughts slip back in. Fortunately, with Stress Ball, you can interact with your phone and clear your mind with exercises, fidgets and videos within the app. There are five different tabs you can use to calm down: Breathe, Fidget, ChillTok, Reflect

In the Breathe tab, there are breathing exercises to help you take deep breaths and calm down. The phone also vibrates and provides various animations to distract your thoughts.

In the Fidget tab, there are virtual fidgets and toys you can play with to distract your mind and let out all of your anxious energy on the app. The fidgets also provide vibration and audio feedback to help you feel more relaxed.

In the ChillTok tab, you can *mindfully* scroll through super calming videos of nature, abstract art, etc. This will help you keep your mind off of anxious thoughts while healthily calming down instead of with social media content.

In the Reflect tab, you can talk through your feelings with StressBot, a virtual therapist! You can always swipe through a lot of positive quotes!

Have a great time using Stress Ball and we hope you find which options work the best for relieving your anxiety!

description:
How many negative thoughts have been endlessly repeating in your mind? Daily affirmations help rewire our brains, build self-esteem, and change negative thought patterns. Empower yourself by verbally affirming your dreams and ambitions. Choose from many daily intentions and set reminders to be delivered throughout the day.

Positive affirmations help make major shifts in your mindset, and they also serve as prompts and daily reminders about what you‚Äôre truly capable of, ensuring every day is an amazing day.

An affirmation is a simple but powerful statement that helps to strengthen the connection between your conscious and unconscious mind. The more you strengthen this connection, the more resilient you‚Äôll be when you experience difficult or challenging circumstances.

As Buddha wisely said: you become what you believe. And the best way to strengthen your resilience is to practice affirmations every single day.


There are many benefits to using affirmations as part of your daily morning routine:

- They help increase your awareness of your thoughts and words, making it easier to recognize the negative and self-doubting thought patterns holding you back.
- Affirmations define your focus. When you focus your energy on the things you want, like achieving your goals, the positive, uplifting, and good, you‚Äôre creating an abundance mindset and strengthening your resolve to make it happen.
- They open you up to possibility. Too often we get stuck in the ‚Äòimpossible‚Äô mindset, but affirmations flip this on its head. When you begin to positively affirm what is actually possible, a whole world of opportunity opens up to you.

*It works on Wear OS: you can use it on your watch.
